By Chibuike Nwabuko Abuja (Sundiata Post) – Nigeriaa Centre for Disease Control (NCDC) has confirmed 476 new cases of COVID-19 in the country, bringing the total number of confirmed cases to 50,964. The NCDC made this known via its verified Twitter handle @NCDCgov on Thursday. The health agency also reported that  7 deaths were recorded in Nigeria. “Till date, 50964 cases have been confirmed, 37569 cases have been discharged and 992 deaths have been recorded in 36 states and the Federal Capital Territory. “The 476 new cases are reported from 18 states- Lagos (235), FCT (44), Kaduna (41), Borno (33), Plateau (28), Abia (13), Edo (13), Rivers (12), Imo (11), Oyo (10), Kano (9), Kwara (7), Enugu (5), Katsina (5), Gombe (4), Ogun (4), Nasarawa (1), Zamfara (1),” the NCDC said. See the breakdown of cases by state below By Chibuike Nwabuko Abuja (Sundiata Post) - A total of 193 new cases of COVID-19 were recorded in Nigeria on Thursday, the Nigeria Centre for Disease Control (NCDC) has announced. This brings the total number of confirmed COVID-19 cases in the country to 5,162. The NCDC made this known via… May 15, 2020 In "Top Stories" By Abujah Racheal ABUJA - Nigeria has announced 575 new COVID-19 cases in the country as total infections from the virus rise to 33,153. The Nigeria Centre for Disease Control (NCDC) made this known on its official twitter handle on Monday . The NCDC said that the new confirmed cases as… July 14, 2020 In "Top Stories" By Chibuike NwabukoAbuja (Sundiata Post) - The Nigeria Centre for Disease Control (NCDC) on Monday confirmed 288 new cases of COVID-19 in the country, bringing the total number of COVID-19 infection to 44,129. The NCDC which released the report via its verified Twitter handle informed that 288 new confirmed cases… August 4, 2020 In "News"